  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Mechanism | Add Mechanism (Editor)</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">What is a Mechanism?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">A <text styleclass="VariableName">Mechanism</text>, in the context of the <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Mechanism</text> commands, is a <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text> and its <text styleclass="Interface">name-tab</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">Use <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editors</text> to add <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text>, <text styleclass="Element">Joints</text>, <text styleclass="Element">Cams</text>, <text styleclass="Element">Gears</text>, <text styleclass="Element">Belts</text>, ... to design your machine. </para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="VariableName" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:21px;">IMPORTANT: Gravitational Vector ( g = 9.81665 m/s/s )</para>
    <para styleclass="VariableName" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:21px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:135px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-GRAVITY-VECTOR.ipp" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text style="color:#ff0000;">The </text><text styleclass="Interface2" style="color:#ff0000;">Gravity Vector</text><text style="color:#ff0000;"> is in the negative Y-axis direction (Green Arrohead in the </text><text styleclass="Interface" style="color:#ff0000;">Model-Editor</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">Before you add the <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">first</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text>, to a <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text>, consider the type of machine. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">For example, if your machine has a horizontal indexing or rotating table, add the <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text> for the table to the <text styleclass="Interface2">Top</text><text styleclass="Element"> Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, or a </text><text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> that is parallel to the </text><text styleclass="Interface2">Top</text><text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Add Mechanism-Editor</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="5" colcount="2">
